operator._comment: Resource should be a streak plate
operator.description: Miniprep (QIAprep Spin Miniprep Kit ) and isolate plasmids pAN3928, pAN4036, pAN1201, and pAN1717  from provided plate streaks
operator.name: Prepare Plasmids

operator.description: 3 Transformations (one time - keeping plates for isolates)
operator.name: Transform Plasmids

operator.description: The day after transformation, pick single colonies and inoculate into 200 μl of M9 glucose with appropriate antibiotics in a V-bottom 96-well plate (Nunc, Roskilde, Denmark, 249952).
operator.name: Pick

operator.description: Grow single colonies in sealed (Excel Scientific, Inc., AeraSeal, BS-25) V-bottom 96-well plates overnight (16 hours) at 37°C and 1000 RPM in an ELMI Digital Thermos Microplates shaker incubator (Elmi Ltd, Riga, Latvia).
operator.name: Incubate

operator._comment: Need to break this into steps for each dilution. Need units.
operator.description: The next day, dilute the overnight cultures 178-fold by adding 15 μL of culture into 185  μL M9 glucose media, and then 15 μL of that dilution into 185 μL 50 μg/mL kanamycin and 50 μg/mL spectinomycin in a V-bottom 96-well plate.
operator.name: Dilute

operator.description: Grow the diluted cultures in an ELMI shaker incubator at 37 °C and 1000 RPM for three hours.
operator.name: Incubate

operator.description: Branch 1 -> Flow cytometry: Dilute the cultures from Step 6 by adding 15 μL of culture into 185 μL of M9 glucose media.
operator.name: Dilute

operator.description: Branch 1 -> Flow cytometry: Take 3 μL of that dilution and distribute into eight wells with 145 μL inducer-containing M9 glucose media with 50 μg/mL kanamycin and 50 μg/mL spectinomycin in a V-bottom 96-well plate. The eight wells correspond to the inducer conditions (—/—/—), (—/—/+), (—/+/—), (— /+/+), (+/—/—), (+/—/+), (+/+/—), and (+/+/+). Each — or + corresponds to the absence or presence of 5 mM L-arabinose (Sigma-Aldrich, MO, A3256), 2 ng/mL aTc (anhydrotetracycline hydrochloride; Sigma-Aldrich, MO, 37919), and 1 mM IPTG (isopropyl β-D-1- thiogalactopyranoside; Sigma-Aldrich, MO, I6758).
operator.name: Transfer

operator.description: Dilute the cultures from Step 6 by transferring 4.56 μL of culture into 8 Falcon tubes (14 mL round-bottom polypropylene tubes; Corning, MA, 352059) each containing 3 mL of M9 glucose media with appropriate inducers and with 50 μg/mL kanamycin and 50 μg/mL spectinomycin. The inducer conditions have been described above in section 7c.
operator.name: Dilute

operator.description: Grow the cultures containing inducer in an Innova 44 shaker (Eppendorf, CT) at 370C and 250 RPM for five hours.
operator.name: Incubate
